\r\n; ******* Projectile Statistics *******\r\n
; Projectiles describe how and what image to use as the weapon flies\r\n
; to its target. Think of the projectile as the \"delivery method\" used\r\n
; to get the warhead to the desired target.\r\n

\r\n; AA = Can this weapon fire upon flying aircraft (def=no)?\r\n
; AG = Can this weapon fire upon ground objects (def=yes)?\r\n
; AN = Can this weapon fire upon naval objects (def=yes)?\r\n
; AS = Can this weapon fire upon sub-marine objects (def=no)?\r\n
; ASW = Is this an Anti-Submarine-Warfare projectile (def=no)?\r\n
; Acceleration = amount to increase missile speed (def=3)\r\n
; Airburst = Does it try to fly over the target instead of hit it (def=no)?\r\n
; Arcing = Does the bullet travel using an arcing path rather than a straight line? (def=no)\r\n
; Arm = arming delay (def=0)\r\n
; Bouncy = Does it bounce a bit upon impact (def=no)?\r\n
; Cluster = number of explosions attached to projectile [cluster-bomb] (def=1)\r\n
; Color = Color  to use for special remapping projectiles (def = none)\r\n
; CourseLockDuration = How many frames the projectile keep its initial course locked for. (def=0)\r\n
; Degenerates = Does the bullet strength weaken as it travels (def=no)?\r\n
; Dropping = Does it fall from a starting height (def=no)?\r\n
; Level = Does it stay at the same altitude in flight? (Currently also acts as IsTorpedo)\r\n
; Elasticity = \"bounciness\" of the object [should be 0.0 through 1.0] (def=0.75)\r\n
; Image = image to use during flight\r\n
; Inaccurate = Is it inherently inaccurate (def=no)?\r\n
; Inviso = Is the projectile invisible as it travels (def=no)?\r\n
; Parachuted = Equipped with a parachute for dropping from plane (def=no)?\r\n
; Proximity = Does it blow up when near its target (def=no)?\r\n
; ROT = Rate Of Turn [non zero implies homing] (def=0)\r\n
; Ranged = Can it run out of fuel (def=no)?\r\n
; Scalable = Can its animations be tuned up and down on the fly? (def=no)\r\n
; Shadow = If High, does this bullet need to have a shadow drawn? (def = yes)\r\n
; SubjectToCliffs = Can this bullet be stopped by upward cliffs?  No effect on homing projectiles. (def=no)\r\n
; SubjectToElevation = Can this bullet get a range bonus from height?  No effect on homing projectiles.  (def=no)\r\n
; SubjectToWalls = Can this bullet be stopped by walls?  (def=no)\r\n
; VeryHigh = Does it fly at a very high cruise altitude (def=no)?\r\n

